<strong>Test Card Reader</strong>

Case ID: him-001
<!-- Smells: UNVERIFIED STEPS -->
<dl>
    <dt>Insert a media card into the reader</dt>
        <dd>The card is recognised</dd>
    <dt>Open the file manager</dt>
    <dt>Find the media card in the menu on the left. Right click on this and open it</dt>
       <dd>A window opens showing the contents of the card (if any)</dd>
    <dt>Right-click within the window and select Create Document → Create Empty File. Call the file test.txt</dt>
        <dd>test.txt is created</dd>
    <dt>Drag test.txt to the trash can in the left hand menu</dt>
        <dd>test.txt is removed from the card</dd>
    <dt>Close the card window</dt>
    <dt>Eject the card</dt>
        <dd>The icon is removed from the desktop</dd>
    <dt>Repeat for every type of media supported (e.g. CF, SD, MMC, etc.)</dt> 
</dl>


<strong>Reconnect Card Reader and Verify Remounting</strong>

Case ID: him-002
<dl>
    <dt>Insert a media card into the reader</dt>
        <dd>The card is recognised</dd>
    <dt>Click eject</dt>
        <dd>The window disappears</dd>
        <dd>The icon is removed from the desktop</dd>
</dl>

